title: Ann Arbor Spring Training Series 27th Annual
MSU Road Race and Time Trial
description: MSU Collegiate Road Race and Time Trial.  We have eliminated the dirt road for this year.  Instead, we have long open roads which should yield some powerful cross-winds.  The finish is surprisingly hilly, mixing up the finishing leg of the race.  The time trial will be a decided by the strongest and most aerodynamic rider.
course:
Road Race
The Road Race will start at the north end of Every Road heading south.  There is ample parking and little traffic.  The course will follow Every Road, passed Holt Road, until reaching Lamb Road where it will turn right.  Lamb Road will lead to Simmions Road, turning right.  Simmons Road ends at Holt Road where the course will turn right and then almost immediately left onto Dobie Road.  There is a hard banked turn to the right onto Stillman Road, where the course will reconnect with Every Road.  The finish will be before the intersection, and a second lap will be a right turn onto Every Road.
Map Of Course:  http://www.gmap-pedometer.com/?r=4117576


Time Trial
The time trial will be similar to the reverse of the Road race.  The TT will start on Stillman Road heading west.  At Dobie Road the course will take a left and continue until Willoughby Road where it will turn left.  Following Willoughby Road, it will turn left on Every Road, finishing where the Road Race started.  Each racer will do two laps.
Map Of Course: http://www.gmap-pedometer.com/?r=4162456
registration: Registration will open from 8:30am-12:00pm and 2:00pm-4:00pm.  Registration for each event will close 10 mins prior to event start.  Registration will be located several feet from the start and staging.
directions:
The race start and parking is located at: N Every Rd & Stillman Rd
Alaiedon, MI 48854

Try to approach from the east, as the race is held on the west side of the parking area.

title: University of Michigan Race
description: The race will be held at the Waterford Hills racetrack, located in Clarkston, MI. The racetrack is well known in the area as being a fantastic course.
course: The 1.5 mile course features several sweeping turns and a hill small enough for the sprinters to power up but large enough to slowly wear out the pack. It finishes on a flat with plenty of space for a large sprint.
registration: Registration opens at 8:00 am and closes 15 minutes prior to each race. $13 per licensed rider, with $10 one-day licenses available.
directions: The racetrack is at 4770 Waterford Road, Clarkston, MI 48346. If taking I-75 from Saturday\'s race, take exit 93 to US-24 S/Dixie Hwy. Turn left at Waterford Road.

title: Pontiac Lake Time Trial
course: The race course is an approximate 10 mile loop with a great combination of single & double track trails, fast flats, challenging climbs and technical sections. If you have enjoyed racing the Pontiac Lake trail in the past, you will surely enjoy it again!
directions:

Parking and race start are on the north side of Gale Road just west of Park Office Entrance.

Tour Des Lacs
description:
Tour Des Lacs Charity Cycling Ride
About This Event:
The 8th Annual Cyclefit Tour Des Lacs will take cyclists through the incredible landscapes of the Fenton area. The routes meander along revealing many of the lakes our area is known for ~with just enough climbing to make you earn your way to the food/beverage at the end. This casual ride is for everyone at every fitness level. 100% of the proceeds are donated to Mott Childrens Hospital, Ann Arbor. The official mass-start for all tours is 8:00am for guaranteed SAG and Hydrations Station support, but cyclists are free to start their ride anytime before 10:00am. All participants will receive a commemorative gift (TDL pint glasses!). The Team with the most participants will earn their name on the traveling trophy. Come sporting your team\'s spirit! Also available for purchase are exclusive TDL men\'s and women\'s cycling jersey.
course:
Start Line: 15K, 50K, 100K & 100 Miles 
Course: All routes share the same finish line after the infamous LiveStrong Climb. The Tour des Lacs meanders around 9 different area lakes hence its name in English Tour of the Lakes. Dont miss the sunflower fields!!
Open Route: All road rules apply
registration:
Entry Fees:
$20. 15K, 50K, 100K & 100 Mile routes, before July 29th
$25. For all routes after July 29th
Commemorative Tour Des Lacs pint glass!! 
Bike Drawing: Pre-registered riders are also entered to win a brand-spanky-new beach cruiser bicycle!
notes:
RIDE A BIKE, SAVE A HEART!
100% of the proceeds are donated to Mott Childrens Hospital, Ann Arbor. 
www.TourDesLacs.org

title: cherry-roubaix cruiser ride, kids fun ride, charit
description:
Charity Ride is a 20, or 40 mile supported ride with road marshals, law enforcment, medical support and signs. 
Kids Ride is a short ride for kids 4-6 and 7-10 that are escorted by \"Captain America\" on a closed crit course, with volunteers.
The Cruiser Classic is a 4 person relay ride once around the closed crit course to promote the Cherry Industry (so they pass a cherry pie and put it in their mandatory basket)and the different organizations in the Grand Traverse Area...the best costumed theme wins a traveling trophey they can proudly display. This is a hilarious spectacle and we have limited it to 15 teams.
course:
The Charity Ride is on quiet roads that are well travelled cyclists and they are escorted out of town to those roads, SAG vehicles, etc. Rules of the road and saftey tips are in their packets.
The Kids Ride and Cruiser Classic are on a closed crit course between Crit Races and have road marshals.

title: Cherry- Roubaix Criterium and State Championship R
GR Cycling Classic & USAC Pro Crit Nat Champ
2011 Herman Miller Grand Cycling Classic Challenge
CXpreX-Ann Arbor
description:
3 race cyclocross clinic to prepare for the upcoming CX season.  There will be a training session before each race with short practice drills and guidance from experienced cyclocross racers.  

Beginners are very welcome.  This is the place to learn about this fun sport.
course: These sessions will be held twice at Leslie Park and once at Buhr Park, both in Ann Arbor.  The courses will be set up to prepare you for that wonderful anaerobic feeling you get during a regular season race.  This is lung and leg prep for the real thing.
registration: Register online or just show up and give us your money.
notes:
There will be A and B level races and clinics for all levels.  The clinics will include a focus on skills--barriers, run-ups, getting on and off the bike, sprints, bike handling--as well as strategies for efficiency during a race. 

The skills you develop in cyclocross can help you in any other kind of riding that you do--road, mtb, track.  Plus, it\'s a great way to keep up the fitness in the fall.

title: Tour of the White Pine Trail 2011
MiSCA & MMBA Burchfield Park Time Trial
description: Time Trial to test your skills on a twisty technical course.  A lot of obstacles, a lot of fun!!  You do not need to be a member of  MiSCA or the MMBA to race.
course: The loop will be approximately 10-12 miles and will take about 60-75 minutes to complete.  The course is mostly tight and twisty, but there are a few sections that are fast with sweeping turns.  Most obstacles have bypasses for beginner riders, but some may require a quick dismount.  The Middle School division will use a modified course that is slightly shorter and less technical than the Adult, JV and Varsity.  Students may compete in higher divisions than their current grade level.
registration:
REGISTRATION:     Opens at 8:30 am 
Registration will be held in the North Bluff Pavilion. Follow the signs once you are in the park.  Held Under USAC Event Permit #2989
directions: Burchfield Park is at 881 Grovenburg Rd. in Holt, MI  48842 (Lansing area)
